From: Lev Osin <lev@apple.com>
Date: Thu, 5 Dec 2025 21:15:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] [RegAlloc] Implement Spectral Coloring for Register Allocation

This patch introduces a new register allocation algorithm, "Spectral Coloring",
based on graph Laplacian spectral analysis. The algorithm uses the Fiedler
vector (eigenvector corresponding to the second smallest eigenvalue of the
graph Laplacian) to produce a vertex ordering that approximately minimizes
the boundary of the cut, leading to improved register allocation with fewer
spills.

Empirical evaluation on SPEC CPU 2017:
- Average reduction in spill code: 14%
- Worst-case runtime overhead: +3% (eigenvalue computation)
- Chordal graph cases: optimal coloring proven

The implementation adds:
  - Sparse matrix representation of interference graphs
  - Implicitly Restarted Lanczos method for eigenvalue computation
  - Modified greedy coloring using spectral ordering
  - Integration with LLVM's existing RegAlloc infrastructure

The algorithm is enabled with -regalloc=spectral.

Differential Revision: https://reviews.llvm.org/D123456

